His praises must be sounded; and God chose the children to do it. Had the voices of these rejoicing children been silenced, the very pillars of the temple would have cried out in the Saviour's praise.  {SJ 91.10}  

Chap. 15 - At the Passover Supper

     The Children of Israel ate the first Passover supper at the time of their release from bondage in Egypt.
